{
  "texts": [
    "Koumoutsakos 2019)",
    "Computes the similarity between the current transition and past experiences to skip gradients from those too unlikely with the current policy.",
    "It regulates policy changes within a trust region of the replayed behaviors, limits the fraction of far-policy samples in the buffer, and computes gradient estimates only from near-policy experiences.",
    "SLER (Li et al. 2021) Multiple tasks in sequence.",
    "Proposes a short-term ER to retain current task experience and a long-term ER to keep all past experiences to achieve continual learning."
  ]
